 What Where Find Jobs Advanced Job Search Senior Product Director - Identity Zeta Global 31 reviews Los Angeles, CA 90001 Zeta Global 31 reviews Read what people are saying about working here. Job details Job Type Full-time Full Job Description Zeta Global is seeking a senior product director to lead development, planning, and delivery of products for Zeta's Identity ecosystem. Zetaâ€™s Data Cloud transforms billions of data signals into meaningful marketing and advertising outcomes, and resolution, reach, and accuracy of our core identity platform is at the center of it all. We're looking for a product leader with deep understanding of identity to build products that can change the way the world's top brands understand their customers. 
Responsibilities 
Develop, maintain, and communicate a strategic roadmap for aspects of Zeta's Identity Graph, collaborating with design, engineering, data science, product managers, and business teams to prioritize, and develop impactful technologies, balancing business objectives, client needs, and innovative product vision. 
Lead, manage, and mentor a small team of product managers aligned to the Zeta Data product, ensuring productive and aligned progress toward company and team objectives. 
Drive global product definition, planning, market positioning, and product design (including writing PRDs) of new initiatives and enhancements to the Zeta Marketing Platform, ensuring alignment of cross-functional development, marketing, sales, and operations teams across the full lifecycle of products. 
Manage development timelines and ensure consistent, high quality, delivery of usable and effective data products. 
Inform and develop Zeta's technology platform infrastructure in partnership with engineering through market, industry, and technology research. 
Act as a leading evangelist of Zeta's data products and participate in customer advisory board sessions and discussions with clients, Zeta executives, thought leaders and market analysts. 
Qualifications 
We are looking for people who have: 
At least five years of experience overseeing probabilistic and deterministic identity products in marketing, analytics, or digital advertising; a computer science undergraduate degree or equivalent, plus hands-on software engineering experience is a plus. 
A proven track record of solving complex technical problems and partnering with agile engineering teams to translate customer needs into impactful products. 
Strong knowledge of identity fundamentals including data compliance and governance, graph database technologies, data analysis and hygiene. 
Fluidity with data and transforming them into insightful stories that can inform a product roadmap. 
#LI-MC1 
